{
  "stem": "3022.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He says, hurry up, otherwise I'll kill you, you dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And this was the child that the Ukrainian guards were telling us that his father gave him a handgun to shoot children.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In 1944-- Did",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Whether it was story-- I read the book, and I tried to find any documentation on that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's nothing mentioned on that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whether it was only stories that the Ukrainians were telling it or it was a fact, I have no way to substantiate it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This particular man, as I told you, had two matching horses.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one night, a friend of mine had a tryst with a-- just shortly before, they brought 100 women to our camp from another labor camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he had a love affair with one of the girls.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went into the barn.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of the horses walked out and walked on the electrified wire-- and by that time, the wires became electrified when the SS took over-- and was killed.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [GERMAN] told us that unless we produce an identical horse, he's going to shoot 20 people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And again, we had to go to our contacts on the outside with some Polish people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they found in the village someplace-- anyhow, after two days, they brought a horse that was a matching horse to this.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a gray-white horse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it cost of course sums of money, to pay off the Poles, in order to get this horse.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This particular Schwammberger was in charge of our transport in July 1944, when the camp was being liquidated.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the advance of the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They started liquidating the camps and moved west.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So on July 24, our camp was moved to Wieliczka, which was a town outside Krakow.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there was another camp there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
